<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 10 at 2:24AM CDT until June 10 at 2:45AM CDT by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 245 AM CDT
FOR MONTAGUE COUNTY...
At 221 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Nocona, moving
southeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Bowie, Nocona, St. Jo, Sunset, Stoneburg and Forestburg.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>This storm has a history of producing winds of 60 to 70 mph. SEEK
SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy structure and stay away from windows!
Wind damage with this storm will occur before any rain or lightning.
Do not wait for the sound of thunder before taking cover.</instruction>
